fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.types

Interface IRelationData

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IData<IRelationType>

    public interface IRelationData
extends IData<IRelationType>
    Provides access to relationship data values.

    Thread-safety: implementations of this interface are not required to be safe for concurrent access. Therefore, processing should generally not be shared between multiple threads.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

    • Method Detail

      • toItem

        IItem toItem()
      throws ItemFetchException
        For relational databases and graph databases, this retrieves the related item, if the item is available.

        A relational database schema may allow this to be null, or even have a value that refers to a deleted target (for example, if there is no ON DELETE CASCADE trigger).

        Note: invoking this method multiple times may be inefficient.

        Returns:
        the edge, if available, or null.
        Throws:
        ItemFetchException - if the item cannot be fetched.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IData.getValue()

      • toEdge

        IEdge toEdge()
      throws EdgeFetchException
        For graph databases, this retrieves the edge (the link with properties that can be traversed to reach the target).

        Note: invoking this method multiple times may be inefficient.

        Returns:
        the edge, if available, or null.
        Throws:

        Since:

      • getCompositeSourceValues

        List<?> getCompositeSourceValues()
        Gets the ordered list of all source data values that define the relationship, ordered by "most restrictive first". The order is consistent with IRelationType.getCompositeTargetCells(), and IRelationType.getCompositeSourceTypes(). The most restrictive element is always the "parent" element of a parent-child relationship (note that the list may contain 1..n) elements).
        Returns:
        the ordered list, never null. For conventional non-composite (scalar, single-value) relationships, this contains a single element (the same as returned by IData.getValue()).
        Since:
        1.0
